  "instructions": [
    "Rinse cod fillets, pat dry, and cut into 2‑inch pieces.",
    "Heat olive oil in the pressure cooker over medium heat; add minced garlic and sauté 30 seconds until fragrant.",
    "Add diced carrot, shredded cabbage, and chopped parsley; cook for 2 minutes to soften slightly.",
    "Stir in smoked paprika, black pepper, and a pinch of sea salt; mix well.",
    "Pour in low‑sodium fish broth and lemon juice; bring to a gentle simmer.",
    "Place cod pieces in the liquid, gently nestle them among the vegetables.",
    "Lock the pressure cooker lid, set to high pressure for 3 minutes (12 psi). Perform a quick release afterward.",
    "While the soup rests, toast almond slivers and pumpkin seeds in a dry skillet until golden (about 2 minutes). Set aside.",
    "Ladle soup into bowls, top with the toasted crunch mix, chopped mint, and serve immediately."
  ],
